δοκεῖ δὲ αὐτῶι τάδε· ἀρχὰς εἶναι τῶν ὅλων ἀτόμους καὶ κενόν, τὰ δ'ἀλλα πάντα νενομίσθαι [δοξάζεσθαι]. (Diogenes Laërtius, Democritus, Vol. IX, 44)

"The first principles of the universe are atoms and empty space; everything else is mere opinion."
Looking from Calypso's Cave onto Ir-Ramla l-Ħamra, the Red Sandy Beach on the northern coast of Gozo.
You can just about spot Calypso Cave on the western side of the bay.
Calypso's Cave. Odysseus is claimed to have been held captive in this cave as concubine to the nymph Calypso. So what's the problem? Where's the drama?
Calypso had promised him immortality if he stayed with her.

View from Calypso's Cave. This is one of the most shot locations in Gozo. 

So if you haven't been there, or been there but didn't take your camera with you, you're free to take this and pretend it's yours :-p.
Anyone seen my sandals? I'm sure I left them by the mouth of the cave last night.

The cave itself is boring, dirty and full of papers and trash. Next to the cave is a gift shop and water to drink and free toilets, but they are also dirty. There is a viewing platform but it is very windy.
View from Tal Mixta Cave in Gozo, Malta.
Be careful if you want to go in, I hit my head pretty bad on one of the low rocks in there.

Inside the cave (now collapsed).

Time has not done this attraction any favours. When I first visited (about 15 years ago) you went down the narrow entrance and had a good "window" looking out to sea and felt the magic of the place. Now, the rocks have tumbled and I can't believe it's a safe place to go. It seems like an accident waiting to happen.
So... #calypsoscave recently collapsed. This is an unofficial view from inside the cave. #gozo

"The cave it's closed! Climb at your own risk! Nice viewpoint, but the cave it's closed since may 2012" @ Calypso Cave: [http://4sq.com/R1Zb55](http://t.co/AB4SgJe1?amp=1) [#foursquare](https://twitter.com/hashtag/foursquare?src=hashtag_click)
Calypso Cave, Gozo, Malta

None of the 26 men at the club bar admitted to ever having met a woman named Calypso. More importantly, there seemed to be a consensus that the publicized site of “Calypso Cave” above the sandy Ramla Bay is a hoax and not the actual Calypso cave.
Another great view from the CAVE that is a much more likely inspiration for the title of Cave of Calypso (the name given to a much smaller cave across the bay).
Calypso’s Cave offers a marvellous panoramic view over Ramla Bay’s red sandy beach.
14 days to leave this paradise and I don't know what to feel !! Rsrsrs

I found Calypsos Cave! Every review I read says this iconic site is caved in and no longer accessible, but I still decided to check it out and am so glad I did. Legend has it this is the same cave from Homers The Oddysey where Calypso kept Odysseus as a prisoner of love on the island for 7 years. . . . . .
